title: Grateful Dead Live at Rainbow Theater on 1981-03-20
lineage: soundboard master cassettes > Nak Dr-1 > Lynx2 Studio Interface 24 bit 48kHz.   Edited and Mastered on the **GEMS** Edit Station MetaData with Tag and Rename TLH for FLAC Level 8
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, CC Rider, Althea, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loser, Minglewood Blues, Candyman-> Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Hard to remember I was at this show when I was 14 ate a strawberry someone gave me in the front row.  I think there had to be something in that strawberry :)

hard to find Most 81 boards don't sound this good

good show

peace
smokin' second set This is scorching.  Post-drums is much hotter than it looks on paper.  Nice to get a sbd.  I think it's a bit fast, esp. first half or so of set 1.
